title: Biden secures Democratic nomination with majority of delegates, NBC News projects
description: President Joe Biden clinched the Democratic presidential nomination Tuesday, NBC News projects, winning a majority of the necessary delegates and setting up what is expected to be a bitter, closely-contested rematch with Donald Trump.

title: Who is Jeff Yass? The billionaire donor with investments in TikTok’s parent company
description: In the pitched battle between TikTok and Washington, few people stand to lose more than Jeff Yass, an American billionaire options trader who has emerged in recent years as a major donor to Republican candidates and causes.

title: Uvalde police chief announces resignation after report on Robb Elementary School shooting
description: The Uvalde, Texas, police chief announced his resignation Tuesday, days after a city council report cleared several officers of wrongdoing in the delayed law enforcement response to the shooting at Robb Elementary School that ended in the deaths of 19 children and two teachers.

title: Trump's newfound opposition to a TikTok ban isn't swaying Republicans
description: The House appears poised to pass a bill to ban TikTok in the U.S. despite Donald Trump's newfound opposition to banning the app.

title: Robert Hur testifies in Biden classified docs hearing
description: Coverage of special counsel Robert Hur's testimony to congress

title: Transcript of Biden's interview with special counsel Robert Hur shows memory lapses — but also detailed exchanges
description: The transcript of President Biden's interview by special counsel Hur, which was reviewed by NBC News, paints a nuanced image on both sides.

title: First aid ship sets sail for Gaza loaded with 200 tons of food
description: The Israeli military said it is still trying to confirm whether it killed one of Hamas’ top commanders in an airstrike.

title: 'Everything's for sale': Trump's TikTok flip-flop follows disturbing pattern
description: Rachel Maddow looks at examples of Donald Trump completely reversing a strongly stated opinion at a time that appears to coincide with a donation or other financial incentive, a situation that is not likely to change given Trump's transactional nature and his growing desperation for money.
